AntiExample.WhyWrong:
Violates Solution Silence (0% — executable code provided directly);
violates Decomposition Completeness (no decomposition at all);
violates Hint Actionability (no hints — the answer is given outright);
violates Prerequisite Ordering (no ordering — problem skips directly to
solution); violates Reasoning Continuity (no dependency links exist
because no steps exist); violates Process Integrity (no Understand,
Decompose, or Self-Refine phases were executed). The user receives an
answer they can copy but gains no transferable problem-solving ability.
